object.script:
cyan={42,252,90,(42)/10,(102)/10,(90)/10} red={150,25,24,10,5,4} pink={253,43,218,10,4,9} white={150,150,150,10,10,10} blue={42,252,218,4,4,11} yellow={225,253,44,23,26,0} t=0 lvl=0 function onTick() lvlp=lvl theme=input.getNumber(1) spd =input.getNumber(2) rps =input.getNumber(3) lvl =input.getNumber(4) cap =input.getNumber(5) bat =input.getNumber(6) mxspd=input.getNumber(7) mxrps=input.getNumber(8) x =input.getNumber(9) show =input.getNumber(10)
on =input.getBool(1) blink=input.getBool(2) use =input.getBool(3) if on then t=math.min(t+1,100) else t=math.max(t-2,0) end c=t/100 if use then hi = 24 else hi = 18 end if theme==0 then dig=cyan elseif theme==1 then dig=red elseif theme==2 then dig=pink elseif theme==3 then dig=white elseif theme==4 then dig=blue else dig=yellow end end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
screen.setColor(dig[4],dig[5],dig[6]) screen.drawRectF(1,1+x,w-2,hi)
screen.setColor(dig[1],dig[2],dig[3],c*255) if lvl/cap>show then fuel="fuel" else fuel=math.floor(lvl).."L" end
screen.drawText(2,4+x,fuel) fuelblip=math.floor(lvl/cap*4+0.5) for i=0,fuelblip,1 do if i<fuelblip then screen.drawRect(2+i*5,2+x,3,0) elseif i==fuelblip and blink then screen.drawRect(2+i*5,2+x,3,0) end end
screen.drawText(2,13+x,"batt.") batteryblip=math.floor(bat*4+0.5) for i=0,batteryblip,1 do if i<batteryblip then screen.drawRect(2+i*5,11+x,3,0) elseif i==batteryblip and blink then screen.drawRect(2+i*5,11+x,3,0) end end if use then lps = math.min(math.floor((lvlp-lvl)*60*10),999) if string.len(lps)<2 then unit="dl/s"elseif string.len(lps)<3 then unit="dls" else unit="dl" end screen.drawText(2,19+x,lps..unit) end screen.drawLine(0,h-1,w,h-1) end

cyan={42,252,90,(42)/10,(102)/10,(90)/10} red={150,25,24,10,5,4} pink={253,43,218,10,4,9} white={150,150,150,10,10,10} blue={42,252,218,4,4,11} yellow={225,253,44,23,26,0} t=0
function onTick() theme=input.getNumber(1) spd =input.getNumber(2) rps =input.getNumber(3) lvl =input.getNumber(4) cap =input.getNumber(5) bat =input.getNumber(6) mxspd=input.getNumber(7) mxrps=input.getNumber(8) x =input.getNumber(9) gear =math.floor(input.getNumber(11)+0.5) time =input.getNumber(12)
on =input.getBool(1) blink=input.getBool(2) mulR =input.getBool(5) mulD =input.getBool(6) if on then t=math.min(t+1,100) else t=math.max(t-2,0) end c=t/100 if theme==0 then dig=cyan elseif theme==1 then dig=red elseif theme==2 then dig=pink elseif theme==3 then dig=white elseif theme==4 then dig=blue else dig=yellow end end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
screen.setColor(dig[4],dig[5],dig[6]) --bg screen.drawRectF(1,1+x,29,17)
screen.setColor(dig[1],dig[2],dig[3],c*255) --fg
for i=0,math.min(26,math.floor(rps/mxrps*26+0.5)),1 do screen.drawRectF(2+i,math.max(2,8-i)+x,1,1) end strng = math.floor(rps*60+0.5) len = string.len(strng) screen.drawText(30-len*5,4+x,strng)
--gearD=gear>0 and mulD and gear or gear>0 and "D" or mulR and gear<0 and ("R"..math.abs(gear)) or gear<0 and "R"or "N" screen.drawRectF(2,10+x,1,7) --screen.drawText(4,11+x,gearD) screen.drawLine(0,h-1,w,h-1)
screen.drawText(5,25,string.format("%02d",math.floor(time*24))..":"..string.format("%02d",math.floor(time*24*60%60)))
screen.setColor(dig[1]/4,dig[2]/4,dig[3]/4,c*255) --fg sec. for i=0,3-len,1 do screen.drawText(10+i*5,4+x,"0") end screen.drawText(15-11,11+x,"rpm")
end

cyan={42,252,90,(42)/10,(102)/10,(90)/10} red={150,25,24,10,5,4} pink={253,43,218,10,4,9} white={150,150,150,10,10,10} blue={42,252,218,4,4,11} yellow={225,253,44,23,26,0} t=0 pos=0 function lne(x) y=1-math.abs(x*2%(2*1)-1) return y end
function onTick() theme=input.getNumber(1) spd =input.getNumber(2) rps =input.getNumber(3) lvl =input.getNumber(4) cap =input.getNumber(5) bat =input.getNumber(6) mxspd=input.getNumber(7) mxrps=input.getNumber(8) x =input.getNumber(9)
on =input.getBool(1) blink=input.getBool(2) unit =input.getBool(4) lines=input.getBool(7) if on then t=math.min(t+1,100) else t=math.max(t-2,0) end c=t/100 if unit then km="ms^" un=1 else km="km^" un=3.6 end spdper=math.min(1,spd/(mxspd/un)) pos=(pos+spdper/10)%1 if theme==0 then dig=cyan elseif theme==1 then dig=red elseif theme==2 then dig=pink elseif theme==3 then dig=white elseif theme==4 then dig=blue else dig=yellow end end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear() speedString = math.floor(spd * un+0.5) speedStringLen = string.len(speedString)
screen.setColor(dig[4],dig[5],dig[6]) --bg
screen.drawRectF(1,1+x,5*3+1,7) screen.drawText(18,2+x,km)
screen.setColor(dig[1]/4,dig[2]/4,dig[3]/4,c*255) --fg sec.
screen.drawLine(0,h-1,w,h-1) screen.drawLine(0,h-1,w/2,h/2-1) screen.drawLine(w-1,h-1,w/2-1,h/2-1)
screen.setColor(dig[1],dig[2],dig[3],c*255) --fg
screen.drawText(2-5*speedStringLen+15,2+x,speedString)
screen.drawLine(spdper*w/2-0.5, h-1-h/2*spdper, w-math.ceil(spdper*w/2-0.5), h-1-h/2*spdper)
if lines and spd>10 then ya=math.max(pos*h,h/2) yb=lne(pos)*h/2 screen.drawRectF(w/2-1,ya,2,yb) screen.drawLine(w-ya-1,ya,w-ya-yb-1,ya+yb) screen.drawLine(ya,ya,ya+yb,ya+yb) end
screen.setColor(dig[1]/4,dig[2]/4,dig[3]/4,c*255) --fg sec2. for i=1,3-speedStringLen,1 do screen.drawText(2+i*5-5,2+x,"0") end
end

object.script:
cyan={42,252,90,(42)/10,(102)/10,(90)/10} red={150,25,24,10,5,4} pink={253,43,218,10,4,9} white={150,150,150,10,10,10} blue={42,252,218,4,4,11} yellow={225,253,44,23,26,0}
theme=blue
frame=0 frameT=0 loading={"-" , "\\ " , "|" , "/"} fuelA,fuelB=0,0 t=0 bri=0 function onTick() engine = input.getBool(1) rps = input.getNumber(1) fuel = input.getNumber(2)
t=t+1 if t>=30 then fuelB=fuelA fuelA=fuel t=0 end
if frameT>=30 then frame=(frame+1)%4 frameT=0 end
on=input.getBool(2) if on then bri=math.min(bri+1,100) else bri=math.max(bri-2,0) end
end
function onDraw() c = bri/100 h = screen.getHeight() w = screen.getWidth() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
screen.setColor(theme[1],theme[2],theme[3],c*255)
screen.drawRect(2,2+math.floor((c-1)*10),w-4,8) if not engine then screen.drawText(4,4+math.floor((c-1)*10),"Engine off") screen.drawText(2,12,"[Start]") else if rps<0.5 then screen.drawText(4,4+math.floor((c-1)*10),"Starting"..loading[frame+1]) frameT=frameT+1
else screen.drawText(4,4+math.floor((c-1)*10),"Engine on") screen.drawText(2,12,"rps") screen.drawText(2,18,math.floor((rps*10)+0.5)/10) end
if engine and rps>1 then screen.drawText(32,12,"fuel") screen.drawText(32,18,math.floor(fuel*100+0.5).."%") end
if engine and rps>10 then screen.drawText(2,26,"fuel left") screen.drawText(2,32,math.floor(fuel/(fuelB-fuelA)/2/60).."min") screen.drawText(2,40,"[Stop]") end end
end

cyan={42,252,90,(42)/10,(102)/10,(90)/10} red={150,25,24,10,5,4} pink={253,43,218,10,4,9} white={150,150,150,10,10,10} blue={42,252,218,4,4,11} yellow={225,253,44,23,26,0}
theme=blue
bri=0 vs=0 header=" " text=" " function onTick() on=input.getBool(2)
x=input.getNumber(3) y=input.getNumber(4) v=input.getNumber(5) a=input.getNumber(6) distance = input.getNumber(10) state = input.getNumber(11) vs = vs*0.95+v*0.05 zoom = math.max(math.abs(vs/10),1)
if on then bri=math.min(bri+1,100) else bri=math.max(bri-2,0) end
ap = input.getBool(5) wp1 = not input.getBool(6)
if state < 1.5 then text = "[Go to:]" elseif state > 2.5 then text = "[wp1][wp2]" else text = "[ap off]" end
spots = input.getBool(7) end
function onDraw() local textoffset=0 c = bri/100 h = screen.getHeight() w = screen.getWidth() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if ap and wp1 then header = "AP - WP1" elseif ap and not wp1 then header = "AP - WP2" else header = "AP off" end
--map screen.setMapColorOcean(0, 0, 0) screen.setMapColorShallows(blue[4]/3,blue[5]/3,blue[6]/3) screen.setMapColorLand(blue[4],blue[5],blue[6]) screen.setMapColorGrass(blue[6]/3, blue[6]/2, blue[6]) screen.setMapColorSand(blue[4]+20, blue[5]+20, blue[6]+20) screen.setMapColorSnow(blue[6]/2, blue[6]/2, blue[6])
screen.drawMap(x,y,zoom) --map
screen.setColor(theme[1],theme[2],theme[3],c*255)
screen.drawRect(2,2+math.floor((c-1)*10),w-4,8)
screen.drawText(4,4+math.floor((c-1)*10),header)
screen.drawText(2,12,"alt:"..math.floor(a+0.5))
if ap then if distance<1000 then screen.drawText(2,18,math.floor(distance+0.5).."m") else screen.drawText(2,18,math.floor(distance/100)/10 .."km") end textoffset=textoffset+6 end
screen.drawTextBox(0,h-6,w,6,text,0,-1) if spots then screen.setColor(25,50,100,c*255) screen.drawText(1,18+textoffset,"[=D]") else screen.setColor(100,25,50,c*255) screen.drawText(1,18+textoffset,"[~D]") end end
